}} 'Preston North End Football Club' (often shortened to 'PNE') is an English
professional association football club located in the Deepdale area of the city
of Preston, Lancashire. They currently play in League One, the third tier of the
English football league system.

Preston North End were founding members of the Football League and completed the
inaugural season unbeaten to become the first league champions. In the same
season, Preston won the FA Cup without conceding a goal, becoming the first club
to achieve the English football "Double".

Preston's feat of completing the 1888-89 season unbeaten in both the League and
Cup has not been equalled since, earning them the nickname "The Invincibles".

Preston's most recent major trophy win was their FA Cup victory over
Huddersfield Town F.C. in 1938.

Many important players have played for the club over the years, including Tom
Finney, Bill Shankly, Tommy Docherty, Bobby Charlton, David Beckham, Jon Macken,
David Healy, Richard Cresswell, David Nugent, Ricardo Fuller, and Graham
Alexander.

Based on results achieved during 112 seasons in the Football League from 1888â89
to 2010â11, Preston were ranked as the fourth most-successful English football
club of all time domestically, while only Notts County had played more Football
League games than Preston. {{cite web
